I'm currently revising the `handleFacilityClick` method to streamline human recycling. I am removing selected humans from the `selectedHumanIds` set immediately after they are recycled. This enhances state consistency. I'm confirming that the new changes don't introduce any new bugs.

**Improving State Consistency**

I've just finished revising the `handleFacilityClick` method. The loop is now working to recycle selected humans, improving efficiency, and ensuring that the `selectedHumanIds` is properly updated after recycling. The code now removes the selected humans from the `selectedHumanIds` set immediately after recycling them, guaranteeing that the state remains valid. The unit tests are now all passing.


**Updating Interactions**

I'm now integrating the new facility-specific behaviors based on the updated `handleFacilityClick` interactions. This includes ensuring proper rendering and functionality. The recent focus is on coordinating the visual and functional aspects of selecting and moving humans. It's a key part of the UI, and I am focused on making sure everything feels consistent and responds well to user input.

```
<file>
    <name>src/components/FacilityRoom.tsx</name>
    <content>
        // ... imports

        interface FacilityRoomProps {
          type: FacilityType;
          humans: Human[];
          selectedHumanIds: Set&lt;string&gt;;
          onHumanClick: (id: string) =&gt; void;
          onFacilityClick: (type: FacilityType) =&gt; void;
          progress?: number;
        }

        const FacilityRoom: React.FC&lt;FacilityRoomProps&gt; = ({
          type,
          humans,
          selectedHumanIds,
          onHumanClick,
          onFacilityClick,
          progress = 0
        }) =&gt; {
          const config = FACILITY_CONFIG[type];
          const hasSelection = selectedHumanIds.size &gt; 0;

          const getIcon = () =&gt; {
            switch (type) {
              case FacilityType.POWER:
                return &lt;Zap className="w-6 h-6" /&gt;;
              case FacilityType.FOOD:
                return &lt;Utensils className="w-6 h-6" /&gt;;
              case FacilityType.BIOREACTOR:
                return &lt;Trash2 className="w-6 h-6" /&gt;;
              case FacilityType.CLAW:
                return &lt;Cog className="w-6 h-6" /&gt;;
              case FacilityType.HOSPITAL:
                return &lt;Heart className="w-6 h-6" /&gt;;
              default:
                return null;
            }
          };

          return (
            &lt;div
              className={`relative bg-gray-700 w-24 h-24 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-600 transition-colors duration-200 ${
                config.type === 'bioreactor' &amp;&amp; hasSelection ? 'bg-red-500' : ''
              }`}
              onClick={() =&gt; onFacilityClick(type)}
            &gt;
              &lt;div className="absolute top-1 left-1"&gt;{getIcon()}&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div className="relative w-full h-full flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-2"&gt;
                {config.type === 'bioreactor' &amp;&amp;
                  &lt;div className="absolute top-0 right-0 p-1 text-xs bg-red-800 rounded-bl"&gt;
                    Recycle!
                  &lt;/div&gt;
                }
                &lt;div className="text-center text-xs"&gt;{config.label}&lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div className="flex flex-row flex-wrap justify-center items-center h-16 w-full gap-0.5"&gt;
                  {humans.map(human =&gt; (
                    &lt;HumanUnit
                      key={human.id}
                      human={human}
                      onClick={onHumanClick}
                      isSelected={selectedHumanIds.has(human.id)}
                    /&gt;
                  ))}
                &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
          );
        };

        export default FacilityRoom;
    </content>
</file>
```


